definition.value: A  piperidine alkaloid that is decahydronaphtho[2,3-c]furan-1(3H)-one substituted by a methyl group at position 3 and a 2-[(2R,6S)-1,6-dimethylpiperidin-2-yl]ethenyl group at position 4. It has been isolated from the bark of Australian magnolias.

A biflavonoid that is apigenin substituted by a 4-(5,7-dihydroxy-4-oxo-4H-chromen-2-yl)phenoxy group at position 6. A diflavonyl ether, it is isolated from Rhus succedanea and has been found to possess significant cytotoxic potential.
A lignan that is dihydrofuran-2(3H)-one (gamma-butyrolactone) substituted by a 3,4-methylenedioxybenzyl group at positions 3 and 4 (the 3R,4R-diastereoisomer).
An indole alkaloid isolated from the Amaryllidaceae family and has been shown to exhibit cytotoxic activity.
A deoxygluconolactone with the hydroxy group at position 2 replaced by hydrogen.
An aldonolactone derived from glucose with one or more of the hydroxy groups replaced by hydrogen.
A deoxygluconolactone with the hydroxy group at position 6 replaced by hydrogen.

Any one of a family of large lipopeptides that are inhibitors of the enzyme 1,3-beta-glucan synthase, thus damaging fungal cell walls. Echinocandins are fungicidal against most Candida spp and fungistatic against Aspergillus spp.
A deoxygalactonolactone with the hydroxy group at position 6 replaced by hydrogen.
An aldonolactone derived from galactose with one or more of the hydroxy groups replaced by hydrogen.
Conjugate base of (3S)-3-hydroxy-L-aspartic acid.
Tetraanion of (E)-cinnamoyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups.
An acyl-CoA oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate, diphosphate and carboxy groups of (R)-2-benzylsuccinyl-CoA.
An acyl-CoA(4-) that is the tetraanion of (R)-phenyllactoyl-CoA, arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups.
Conjugate base of 3-(4-oxo-4,5-dihydro-1H-imidazol-5-yl)propanoic acid.
Decaanion of 1L-myo-inositol 1,2,3,4,6-pentakisphosphate.
The dianion obtained by removal of the two acidic protons from the phosphate group of 2-amino-5-formylamino-6-(1-D-ribosylamino)pyrimidin-4(3H)-one 5'-phosphate.
Dianion of 2-deoxy-alpha-D-ribose 1-phosphate.
Tetraanion of 2-methylbut-2-enoyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of phosphate and diphosphate groups.
Zwitterionic form of 3,3',5'-triiodo-L-thyronine.

A singly-charged anionic phospholipid that is the conjugate base of 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine, in which the carboxy and phosphate groups are anionic and the amino group is cationic; major species at pH 7.3.
Conjugate base of 4-carboxymethylenebut-2-en-4-olide.
Zwitterionic form of 4-fluoro-L-threonine.
The conjugate base of a 6-(N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl)-1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol compound.
Dianion of (-)-usnic acid.
Dianion of beta-D-fructofuranose 2-phosphate.
Dianion of beta-L-fucose 1-phosphate.
Dianion of N,N'-diacetylchitobiosyldiphosphodolichol.
Conjugate base of N,N-dihydroxy-L-tyrosine.
An acyl-CoA(4-) that is the tetraanion of indol-3-ylacetyl-CoA, arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups.
Dicarboxylate anion of (1S,6R)-2-succinyl-6-hydroxycyclohexa-2,4-diene-1-carboxylic acid.
A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion resulting from the removal of both of the hydrogens from the diphosphate group of GDP-beta-L-fucose.
Dianon of 3,5-dibromo-4-hydroxybenzoic acid arising from deprotonation of both the carboxy and phenolic functions.
Dianion of dTDP-D-galactose.
An acyl-CoA(4-) that is the tetraanion of feruloyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-(3-hydroxyphenyl)propanoic acid.
The conjugate base of a 3-acylpyruvic acid.
Conjugate base of 3-amino-2-oxopropyl phosphate.
An anthocyanidin cation consisting of benzopyrylium with hydroxy substituents at positions 3 and 5, a methoxy group at position 7 and a 4-hydroxy-3,5-dimethoxyphenyl group at position 2.
N(6)-Lipoyl-L-lysine residue protonated on the nitrogen at C-2.
N(6)-(S(8)-aminomethyldihydrolipoyl)-L-lysine residue protonated on both the alpha- and side-chain amino groups.
An N-methyl-L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion derived from N(alpha)-methyl-L-tryptophan.
Conjugate base of 5,7-dihydroxy-4'-methoxyflavone.
Zwitterionic form of agaritine.
A 3-oxoacyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of acetoacetyl-CoA.
Tetraanion of coenzyme A.
